Children's cold and cough medicines are under scrutiny by federal regulators due to insufficient testing in children.
Overdoses are common as many kids are given multiple medications.
Some products have misleading labels, prompting Baltimore officials to advise against using them for children under 5.
The FDA issued warnings about the risks, leading to recalls of certain infant cough remedies.
Safety experts recommend avoiding these medicines for young children altogether.
The FDA is reviewing the safety of cough and cold remedies for children, considering potential bans and stricter labeling requirements.
